			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Recent study on Lute of the Howler<a name="40103"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 15 04 7:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Many dispute the LotH's usefulness. Many claim the exorbitant asking price of traders for this rare piece of equipment is baseless. The truth could not be farther from these claims.
<br />

<br />
I recently made a bard alt and leveled him to 40 (the minimum level a LotH can be right clicked). I went to Dulak Harbor and and chose the scout mobs as the mobs for my test. All conned dark blue.
<br />

<br />
I killed 10 of them in regular form (LotH not in effect). I used various song twists during the kills. Despite my different twisting tactics, each fight ended with me having about 30-40% life left (wearing fungi tunic).
<br />

<br />
My next experiment was to kill 10 of them while in werewolf form. I used various twist lineups in these instances as well. What I found was incredible. Each fight ended with me having about 80-90% life left (wearing fungi tunic).
<br />

<br />
While many may argue that the LotH loses effectiveness as you get higher in level, this is not my arguement. At level 40 the LotH makes you about 100% more effective. Even if this effectiveness wanes at a VERY VERY generous percentage of 10% a level, this makes the lute an incredibly powerful piece of equipment at least until level 50. My guess is the effectiveness decrease is more around 5% a level, thus making the lute highly beneficial to lvl 60.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><IMG SRC="http://www.hometown.aol.com/mudplayerx/images/theslums.gif ">
