				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Recent study on Lute of the Howler<a name="40105"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 15 04 8:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, at a point in your character's life when it has far from maxed stats and possibly sub 1k atk rating, the Lute is a very large boost to atk and the 40% haste is also very nice at that level. However, 40% haste will not be sufficient at L60+. Songs and spells supplant the haste. Str is relatively easy to cap. So basically, you end up with the extra atk and an illusion. It is a primary hand lute, but the mod isn't that good, depending on your point of view. 
<br />

<br />
At L40 your best haste song is hanging around or just above 20%. The lute doubles this. This alone is very significant. It would be even more noticable if you didn't have any item haste. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
