				<td colspan="2"><span> Even at lvl 65 LoTH is effective. Now if your a Bard that mainly groups and you have buffs from other classes than its not that useful to you. If your a Bard that mainly solos then you know there are situations where meleeing is your only choice.
<br />
 Places like Droga, Nurga, PoM, Ssra Temple, The Deep. You can pretty much run up to the named or ph and melee it right in its place. 
<br />
 What I do in these situations(keep in mind I never got my epic I'm a soloer remember but I do have stringed and percussion mods on items) is use the werewolf illusion's 40% haste and my 33% haste gloves. THAT'S 73% HASTE WITHOUT EVEN PLAYING A HASTE SONG!! Now I slow with RoT and twist three DoTs and WoM. If I could use four DoTs without WoM but I find using it to be more effective. I have done much experimenting with this and found this to be my most effective way to melee solo, far superior to twisting for example: WoZ,RCoF,PoV, WoM. You really notice the difference when your illusion wheres off mid battle and your DPS drops. 
<br />
