				<td colspan="2"><span>Mod is 2.2, btw which isn't that great, but I stand by my previous statements on the Lute.
<br />

<br />
Pro:
<br />
Illusion--I don't care what I look like, but I like that it distinguishes me in a crowd.
<br />

<br />
Bobbing and weaving---tells me I'm fighting and the audio associated with it I also refer to rather than the screen. The motion doesn't bother me that much and not at all in 3rd person, lol. You don't need it for that, but I've grown accustomed to and rely apon the audio and visual cues it supples.
<br />

<br />
One hand is great.
<br />

<br />
My attack increase is over 100 without additional buffs, even in shammy buffed groups, maxed str, the atk increase is greater than the ranger buff, and I can't explain why, although they are so close as not to matter.
<br />

<br />
Ditto above comment with enchanter's 'Night's Dark Terror'.
<br />

<br />
Thats all at 65 with a modestly equipped bard.
<br />

<br />
I can tell you that in my swarm kiting days, I often chose to melee Low on Health mobs when they were the last standing and the Lute illusion made a huge difference
<br />

<br />

<br />
Con:
<br />

<br />
low relative mod
<br />

<br />
screws up shrink on raids (illusion is only 36 min). In a raid, take the ranger buff then shrink.
<br />

<br />
I wouldn't pay more that 25k for one, (purchased mine in EC Tunnel for 8k a while back) but then I wouldn't take 80k for mine. So what's that make it worth?
<br />

<br />

<br />
Derail--I sincerely doubt the benefits of a fungi for a level 40 bard other than regen in down time, am I missing something?</span></td>
