				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Recent study on Lute of the Howler<a name="40391"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 17 04 8:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've seen a few people put down the look of the werewolf illusion on this item.
<br />

<br />
I've been playing since EQ came out so I've grown to appreciate old models as well. Actually, I rather like the way it looks. From the constant inspections I receive in crowded zones to the people asking me to cast it on them (I know its self only), I'd gather that other people are impressed with the illusion as well.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As far as the price on the Lute being too high...I kind of agree. I paid 80k for mine, but once you get to a certain level on your main money is kinda useless. Just one more point on price: You rarely ever see a LotH for sale in the bazaar. When you do see them, they are priced high as h*ll. Then it goes back to not seeing one for a very long time again. Doesnt this tell you something? I thought the meaning behind &quot;price check&quot; was the price the item sells for in a short amount of time.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
This is off topic, but someone argued the use of a fungi at lvl 40. While in a fight it only regens about 150-300 hitpoints, you have to look at it from a different standpoint. Thats about a minute I can take away from singing heal song after the fight, not to mention the other minute it saves me as its regenning while i sing the heal song itself. 
<br />

<br />
My bard alt is 43 now (I rarely have time to play) and I already have the Singing Steel Breastplate in the bank (100 point heal in 6 seconds, clicky at level 45). You can bet at level 45 the Fungi is going in a bag. The reason I say a bag is because I am not going to sell it.
<br />

<br />
While the SS breastplate is a wonderful item, but you are unable to sing a song while its in use. In moments where I am going to be constantly twisting, I will still wear the fungi, even after lvl 45. When I am done twisting, I will whip out the SS breastplate and heal.
<br />

<br />
The negative stats can be easily compensated by other gear. Even with the fungi on I have stats close to maxxed.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
