				<td colspan="2"><span>To take the off topic further (and to be contrarian):
<br />

<br />
Quote:
<br />
&quot;This is off topic, but someone argued the use of a fungi at lvl 40. While in a fight it only regens about 150-300 hitpoints, you have to look at it from a different standpoint. Thats about a minute I can take away from singing heal song after the fight, not to mention the other minute it saves me as its regenning while i sing the heal song itself. &quot;
<br />

<br />
My point would be, for the price of the fungi you could purchase something with higher AC and no agi penalty and for non caster mobs avoid as much or more damage than the fungi regens, at that level.
<br />

<br />
It would take a parse to prove it, but I think if you are taking melee damage at 40 the fungus is not the best choice. If I am wrong, it certainly would not be the first time. 
<br />

<br />
Maybe bag it during the fight and put it on whilst singing regen?
<br />
